The News Agency of Nigeria (NAN), reports that Idris was born on Feb. 20, 1936 to the family of Malam Idrisu Auta and Hajiya Aminatu and died around 11:00 a.m. Sunday, at the 44 Nigerian Army Reference hospital in Kaduna.       He was the 18th Emir of Zazzau and the Chairman of Zazzau Emirate Council. He ascended the throne on Feb. 8, 1975 following the demise of Alhaji Muhammadu Aminu, the 17th Emir of Zazzau. He served as private secretary to the Sarkin Zazzau, Muhammadu Aminu.        He became the secretary of the Zaria Native Authority Council in 1965. He took the title of Dan Madamin Zaria in 1973 and became the district head of Zaria and Kewaye in the same year. (NAN)